<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>TSI 03-12-04 - Lower Radiator Outlet Hose</stitle>
    <tsi id="tsi031204" tsitype="truck">
        <tsinumber>03-12-04</tsinumber>
        <replace>
            <tsinumber>02-12-26</tsinumber>
        </replace>
        <tsidate>May, 2003</tsidate>
        <subjectfile>ENGINE</subjectfile>
        <subjectgroup>
            <subject>Lower Radiator Outlet Hose</subject>
        </subjectgroup>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <truckmodelgroup/>

                <truckmodel>7300
                    <daterange>
                        <startdate>07/23/2001</startdate>
                        <enddate>12/01/2002</enddate>
                    </daterange>
                </truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>7400
                    <daterange>
                        <startdate>07/23/2001</startdate>
                        <enddate>12/01/2002</enddate>
                    </daterange>
                </truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>7500
                    <daterange>
                        <startdate>07/23/2001</startdate>
                        <enddate>12/01/2002</enddate>
                    </daterange>
                </truckmodel>
                <engfamgroup/>

                <engfam>DT 466</engfam>
                <engfam>DT 466E</engfam>
                <engfam>530E</engfam>
                <engfam>DT 530</engfam>
                <engfam>HT 530</engfam>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>On some vehicles the lower right side radiator hose can rub against the frame rail causing
                    premature wear. Use of the following procedure and parts will prevent further occurrences.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
        <partsinfo>
            <para>Hose, Radiator Outlet, Lower 3579553C1 Premium, 3580343C1 Silicone</para>
            <para>Nut, Special, M8 Flange HD Nut 40050R1</para>
            <para>Clamp, Pipe, Cushioned, Single 3 In. Diameter 3579770C1</para>
            <para>Bracket Assembly 2585301C1</para>
            <para>Clamps, Shrink band 2506705C1 (2 required)</para>
        </partsinfo>
        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="1">
            <title>Service procedure</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>Allow the engine to cool before attempting to remove the radiator or deaeration tank cap.
                        Always insulate the cap by wrapping it with a thick, heavy cloth. To prevent possible injury
                        from scalding water or steam, do not pull the pressure cap off immediately when it has been
                        loosened to the first notch. Pause momentarily to allow time for pressure to release through the
                        overflow tube.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Drain coolant system.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the lower radiator hose and clamps. See Figure 1.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0312041" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G0212261.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                         scalefitheight="472px"/>
                <caption>Figure 1.</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. CUSHIONED PIPE CLAMP 3579770C1</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. SPECIAL NUT 40050R1 - TORQUE 12 Nm</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. LOWER RADIATOR HOSE - PREMIUM 3579553C1, SILICONE 3580343C1</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. BRACKET ASSEMBLY 2585301C1</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. R&#38;R TWO BOLTS, TORQUE 70 - 80 Nm</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the two lower bolts on the lower right portion of the radiator and install the
                    "Z" shaped bracket. Reinstall the two bolts. Torque 70-80 Nm (51-59 Lbf-ft)
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the new radiator hose with 2 new clamps.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the "P" clip over the radiator hose and secure to the "Z" bracket with the nut
                    provided. Make sure the "P" clip is oriented as shown. Torque nut to 12 Nm (106 In-lbs.).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Refill the coolant system.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </tsi>
</isis>
